<item>
            <title>[POOL-289] Wrong ClassLoader used in BaseGenericObjectPool</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-289</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BaseGenericObjectPool uses Class.forName to load an EvictionPolicy with the thread context ClassLoader.  This does not work in OSGi environments.  If the class load fails with the thread context ClassLoader, the code should attempt to load using the BaseGenericObjectPool class&apos;s ClassLoader as well.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;All&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12776028">POOL-289</key>
            <summary>Wrong ClassLoader used in BaseGenericObjectPool</summary>
